FBIS4-1984 "drchi065_k_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-065 Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Li Peng Issues Rules on Teaching Achievements Li Peng Issues Rules on Teaching Achievements OW0504112094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0534 GMT 17 Mar 94 OW0504112094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service Chinese BFN [Text] Beijing, 17 Mar (XINHUA) -- Premier Li Peng signed State Council Decree No. 151 of the People's Republic of China on 14 March, promulgating the "Regulations on Commending Achievements in Teaching." According to the State Council Decree, the "Regulations" will come into force upon promulgation. The 16-article "Regulations" mainly introduce specific provisions and rules on commending achievements in teaching. The "Regulations" point out: Formulating the regulations is to reward collectives and individuals who have scored achievements in teaching; to encourage educators to conduct studies on education and teaching; and to improve the level of teaching and the quality of schooling. Achievements in teaching mentioned in the "Regulations" represent a teaching program which reflects the creative, original, and practical law of education and teaching; and is effective in improving the level of teaching and the quality of education and achieving the target of training qualified personnel.
